'''Baba Nand Singh ji''' (8 November 1870 – 29 August 1943) was identified as a [[saint]] in the [[Sikhism]] religion. Baba Nand Singh ji was a highly [[Enlightenment (spiritual)|enlightened]] person who acquired a distinct group of followers during his lifetime.

==Enlightenment==

He received spiritual guidance from [[Sant Baba Harnam Singh Ji]].{{cn|date=August 2018}} He was influenced by the teachings of [[Bulleh Shah]] as well.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.sikhawareness.com/topic/14476-baba-bulleh-shah-ji/|title=Baba Bulleh Shah Ji|website=SikhAwareness Forum|language=en-US|access-date=2018-10-12}}</ref>

